### ============================================
### USER SERVICE API - COMPREHENSIVE TEST SUITE
### ============================================
### Base URL: http://localhost:8081
### Updated: March 6, 2026

### ============================================
### 1. USER CREATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 1a. Create User - Valid
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### 1b. Create User - Another Valid User
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Jane Smith",
    "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePassword456!"
}

### 1c. Create User - Invalid Email
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Invalid User",
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### 1d. Create User - Weak Password
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Weak Password User",
    "email": "weak@example.com",
    "password": "weak"
}

### 1e. Create User - Duplicate Email
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Duplicate User",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePassword789!"
}

### ============================================
### 2. AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 2a. Login - Valid Credentials
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### 2b. Login - Invalid Email
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "nonexistent@example.com",
    "password": "AnyPassword123!"
}

### 2c. Login - Invalid Password
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

### 2d. Login - Rate Limit Test (5th attempt)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
    "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### ============================================
### 3. USER UPDATE ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 3a. Update User - Valid (Replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Updated",
    "email": "john.updated@example.com",
    "password": "NewPassword123!"
}

### 3b. Update User - Invalid Email
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### 3c. Update User - Non-existent User
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/users/99999
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Ghost User",
    "email": "ghost@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!"
}

### ============================================
### 4. USER DELETION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 4a. Delete User - Valid (Replace {id} with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/users/2

### 4b. Delete User - Non-existent User
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/users/99999

### ============================================
### 5. CSV UPLOAD ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### 5a. Upload CSV - Valid File
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/upload-csv
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="users.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

name,email
Alice Johnson,alice.johnson@example.com
Bob Williams,bob.williams@example.com
Carol White,carol.white@example.com

------WebKitFormBoundary--

### 5b. Upload CSV - Missing File
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/upload-csv
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary--

### ============================================
### NOTES FOR TESTING
### ============================================
### 1. Replace {id} with actual user IDs from responses
### 2. Copy JWT token from login response for authenticated endpoints
### 3. Wait 15 minutes between rate limit tests
### 4. Use Postman or IntelliJ HTTP Client to run these tests
### 5. Monitor console for performance metrics
### ============================================
